  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Outsource Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>- Provide guidance to team members</p>\n<p>- Book-keeping and preparation of management accounts</p>\n<p>- Preparation of Statutory report (Financial Statements and Notes to the accounts)</p>\n<p>- Preparation of custom reporting packages based on client requirements</p>\n<p>- Where clients are audited, provide support with respect to services provided to the client</p>\n<p>- Cash management and payment processing</p>\n<p>- GST preparation and filing</p>\n<p>- Payroll processing</p>\n<p>· Preparation of payroll details (including calculation of OT, allowances etc.)</p>\n<p>· Payroll disbursement</p>\n<p>· Leave management</p>\n<p>· Preparation of IR8A and IR21</p>\n<p>- Work independently under team manager</p>\n<p>- Propose resolution steps for issues that may arise with clients</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>- A degree in accountancy and/or equivalent professional qualification</p>\n<p>- At least 3.5 years of relevant experience from a professional services firm in an Business Process Outsourcing (Client Accounting) environment</p>\n<p>- Proficient with accounting software</p>\n<p>- Meticulous with good accuracy and attention to detail</p>\n<p>- Good communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>- Good knowledge and understanding of Singapore requirements on accounting, GST and payroll</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
